Vice President Kamala Harris visited the New Flyer Manufacturing Facility in St. Cloud, Minnesota to announce a shift change. She praised Governor Tim Walz for signing a law that will make Minnesota's electricity 100 percent carbon-free by 2040. Harris emphasized the importance of electric buses in reducing pollution and combating climate change. She highlighted the advantages of electric buses, such as their lack of toxic exhaust, lower operating costs, and reliability. The Vice President mentioned the investments made by the Biden administration to put thousands of new electric transit buses on the streets and create jobs. Harris recognized the workers and management at New Flyer for their commitment to building a positive relationship. She concluded by saying that the plant is building not just better buses, but a better America.